  "text": "AFM images of amyloid Ab 1-42 fibrils were acquired for comparison. Fig. 1 B shows the fibrilar structure of Ab peptides incubated at [CITATION_1] C for 72 h. The heights measured for these fibrils were in the same range as the height of the fibrillar structures observed for PG-1. The widths, w, of these fibrils were~10 nm, in agreement with previous reports. Typical lengths were 100-200 nm. Numerous fibrillar structures have been reported for amyloid peptides and have been broadly classified as filaments, protofibrils, type I fibrils, and type II fibrils. Although filaments and protofibrils have typical lengths <100 nm, lengths of fibrils are >100 nm. Based on these lengths, fibrillar structures in this article will be referred to as either filaments or fibrils and no strict distinction between filaments and protofibrils or type I and type 2 fibrils will be made. In addition to the amyloid-like fibrillar structures observed for PG-1, a helical intrafibrillar structure was observed in some of these fibrils (Fig. 1 C) , similar to those reported for the fibrillar structures for Ab and Ab , as well as for other amyloids [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The helical structure observed for the PG-1 fibrils in this work is right-handed, has a periodicity of~41 nm, and has the corrugation amplitude of~0.75 nm.",
